Attribute parsing:

\[(?P<attr>[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)([*^$]?=)"(?P<val>[^"]+)"\]


Class splitting:

\.([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)


ID parsing:

#([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)


üëâ In C++, you only need regex for class splitting (or just String::Split('.')) and contains match. Everything else can be string ops.

